ative interpretation of so-called 'aerial roots'; Meng, X., Ji, T.T., Dong, Y.W., Thermal resistance in sea cucumbers (Apostichopus japonicas) with differing thermal history (2009) Aquaculture, 294, pp. 314-318. , the role of Hsp70; Meola, C., Carlomagno, G.M., Recent advances in the use of infrared thermography (2004) Measurement Science and Technology, 15, pp. R27-R58; Montanholi, Y.R., Swanson, K.C., Palme, R., Assessing feed efficiency in beef steers through feeding behaviour, infrared thermography and glucocorticoids (2010) Animal, 4, pp. 692-701; Morley, S.A., Hirse, T., Pörtner, H.O., Geographical variation in thermal tolerance within Southern Ocean marine ectotherms (2009) Comparative Biochemistry and Physiology, Part A, 153, pp. 154-161; Muñoz, J.L.P., Finke, G.R., Camus, P.A., Thermoregulatory behaviour, heat gain and thermal tolerance in the periwinkle Echinolittorina peruviana in central Chile (2005) Comparative Biochemistry and physiology, Part A, 142, pp. 92-98; Pearson, R.G., Dawson, T.P., Predicting the impacts of climate change on the distribution of species (2003) Global Ecology and Biogeography, 12, pp. 361-371. , are bioclimate envelope models useful?; Peck, L.S., Clark, M.S., Morley, S.A., Massey, A., Rossetti, H., Animal temperature limits and ecological relevance (2009) Functional Ecology, 23, pp. 248-256. , effects of size, activity and rates of change; Petraitis, P.S., Occurrence of random and directional movements in the periwinkle, Littorina littorea (1982) Journal of Experimental Marine Biology and Ecology, 59, pp. 207-217; Pincebourde, S., Sanford, E., Helmuth, B., An intertidal sea start adjusts thermal inertia to avoid extreme body temperatures (2009) The American Naturalist, 174, pp. 890-897; Pörtner, H.O., Climate variations and the physiological basis of temperature dependent biogeography (2002) Comparative Biochemistry and Physiology Part A, 132, pp. 739-761. , systemic to molecular hierarchy of thermal tolerance in animals; Pörtne